        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Windows Server 2008 R2'); ?>
        <p><strong>Windows Server 2008 R2</strong> is a server <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Operating System', 'IT'); ?> produced by <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft', 'C'); ?>. It was released to manufacturing on 22 July 2009 and launched on 22 October 2009. According to the Windows Server Team blog, the retail availability was 14 September 2009. It is built on Windows NT 6.1, the same kernel used with the client-oriented <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Windows 7', 'WIN'); ?>. It is the first 64-bit-only operating system released from Microsoft. Version enhancements include new functionality for Active Directory, new virtualisation and management features, version 7.5 of <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('Microsoft IIS', 'WS'); ?> Web Server and support for up to 256 logical processors.</p>
        <p>There are seven editions: Foundation, Standard, Enterprise, Datacenter, Web, HPC Server, Itanium and Windows Storage Server 2008 R2 (Essentials Edition).</p>
